接口 Iterator<E>

所有已知子接口：
HeaderElementIterator, HeaderIterator, ListIterator<E>, TokenIterator
所有已知实现类：
BasicHeaderElementIterator, BasicHeaderIterator, BasicListHeaderIterator, BasicTokenIterator, CursorJoiner, Scanner, TextUtils.SimpleStringSplitter
public interface Iterator<E>

An Iterator is used to sequence over a collection of objects. Conceptual, an iterator is always positioned between two elements of a collection. A fresh iterator is always positioned in front of the first element. If a collection has been changed since its creation, methods next and hasNext() may throw a ConcurrentModificationException. Iterators with this behavior are called fail-fast iterators.

从以下版本开始：
Android 1.0

方法摘要
 boolean hasNext()
          Returns whether there are more elements to iterate, i.e. whether the iterator is positioned in front of an element.
 E next()
          Returns the next object in the iteration, i.e. returns the element in front of the iterator and advances the iterator by one position.
 void remove()
          Removes the last object returned by next from the collection.
 

方法详细信息

hasNext

boolean hasNext()
Returns whether there are more elements to iterate, i.e. whether the iterator is positioned in front of an element.

返回：
true if there are more elements, false otherwise.
从以下版本开始：
Android 1.0
另请参见：
next()

next

E next()
Returns the next object in the iteration, i.e. returns the element in front of the iterator and advances the iterator by one position.

返回：
the next object.
抛出：
NoSuchElementException - if there are no more elements.
从以下版本开始：
Android 1.0
另请参见：
hasNext()

remove

void remove()
Removes the last object returned by next from the collection. This method can only be called once after next was called.

抛出：
UnsupportedOperationException - if removing is not supported by the collection being iterated.
IllegalStateException - if next has not been called, or remove has already been called after the last call to next.
从以下版本开始：
Android 1.0
